#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 -get-angle

Returns the relative angle from C<$event1> to C<$event2>.

The relative angle is the angle between the X axis and the line
through both events' positions. The rotation direction for positive
angles is from the positive X axis towards the positive Y axis.

This assumes that both events have X/Y information.
If not, this function returns C<False>.

=begin code
method -get-angle ( N-Object() $event2, Num() $angle --> Bool )
=end code

=item $event2; second B<Gnome::Gdk4::Event>.
=item $angle; (transfer ownership: full) return location for the relative angle between both events.

Return value; C<True> if the angle could be calculated.. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for -get-angle

=end comment

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 -get-center

Returns the point halfway between the events' positions.

This assumes that both events have X/Y information.
If not, this function returns C<False>.

=begin code
method -get-center ( N-Object() $event2, Num() $x, Num() $y --> Bool )
=end code

=item $event2; second B<Gnome::Gdk4::Event>.
=item $x; (transfer ownership: full) return location for the X coordinate of the center.
=item $y; (transfer ownership: full) return location for the Y coordinate of the center.

Return value; C<True> if the center could be calculated.. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for -get-center

=end comment

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 -get-distance

Returns the distance between the event locations.

This assumes that both events have X/Y information.
If not, this function returns C<False>.

=begin code
method -get-distance ( N-Object() $event2, Num() $distance --> Bool )
=end code

=item $event2; second B<Gnome::Gdk4::Event>.
=item $distance; (transfer ownership: full) return location for the distance.

Return value; C<True> if the distance could be calculated.. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for -get-distance

=end comment

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-axes

Extracts all axis values from an event.

To find out which axes are used, use L<.get-axes() in class Gnome|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/Gnome#get-axes>
on the device tool returned by L<.get-device-tool()|#get-device-tool>.

=begin code
method get-axes ( Num() $axes, Array[Int] $n-axes --> Bool )
=end code

=item $axes; the array of values for all axes.
=item $n-axes; (transfer ownership: full) the length of array.

Return value; C<True> on success, otherwise C<False>. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for get-axes

=end comment

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-axis

Extract the axis value for a particular axis use from
an event structure.

To find out which axes are used, use L<.get-axes() in class Gnome|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/Gnome#get-axes>
on the device tool returned by L<.get-device-tool()|#get-device-tool>.

=begin code
method get-axis ( GdkAxisUse $axis-use, Num() $value --> Bool )
=end code

=item $axis-use; the axis use to look for.
=item $value; (transfer ownership: full) location to store the value found.

Return value; C<True> if the specified axis was found, otherwise C<False>. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for get-axis

=end comment

=end pod

