#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-device-tool

Returns a L<Gnome::Gdk4::DeviceTool|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/DeviceTool> representing the tool that
caused the event.

If the was not generated by a device that supports
different tools (such as a tablet), this function will
return undefined.

Note: the L<Gnome::Gdk4::DeviceTool|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/DeviceTool> will be constant during
the application lifetime, if settings must be stored
persistently across runs, see L<.get-serial() in class Gnome|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gdk4/Gnome#get-serial>.

=begin code
method get-device-tool (--> N-Object )
=end code

Return value; The current device tool. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for get-device-tool

=end comment

=end pod

