#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 get-history

Retrieves the history of the device that C<$event> is for, as a list of
time and coordinates.

The history includes positions that are not delivered as separate events
to the application because they occurred in the same frame as C<$event>.

Note that only motion and scroll events record history, and motion
events do it only if one of the mouse buttons is down, or the device
has a tool.

=begin code
method get-history ( Array[Int] $out-n-coords --> N-Object )
=end code

=item $out-n-coords; (transfer ownership: full) Return location for the length of the returned array.

Return value; an
  array of time and coordinates. 

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for get-history

=end comment

=end pod

